Phrase: At Victoria's suggestion, we have unlocked all the dungeon cells. So far, there seems to be no harmful consequences, such as monsters being unleashed, but there were more cells than we expected, so we were just in time to escape.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: I think we managed to get everyone out safely.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: The flooding made it more difficult than I thought. My legs don't move as much as I'd like, the bars are heavy and Putra had to swim.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Good work, the big people. Us mini-mums gave up so quickly that we took refuge on the stairs, so we're not so wet from the hips up.

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: I am completely soaked! Your butt and tail bounced me right off and I fell into it!

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Yakky-tan stays by Yoshino's butt day and night.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: The problem lies ahead. Did Anna go to the top of this stone tower instead of going out into the Hole?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I think the former. I hope we will soon find another tower with a small room.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Then there's also the weather. Even if it's raining, it's not convenient if it's Nacht time.
Oh, really? Then I'll make it Nacht for you.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: The lights!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: That was....
Geheheheheh...

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Haaaaaiii~ Long time no see, all of you from the SSS. Canaria, the very dangerous canary, yeah~~

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Canaria!

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Vache, I thought you were trapped in the interstellar worlds...

Name: Canaria
Phrase: That did happen to me, didn't it? That bloody bitch hurt me to death so much.
Canaria appeared from the darkness. She is a member of the Resistance and a dangerous individual with a different agenda to Queenrose and Ricardo.
We had a lot of questions to ask her, but first and foremost we had to solve the problem of rescuing Paddington, who was being held hostage by Canaria.

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Hawawa! What are you doing! I don't taste good!

Name: Victoria
Phrase: You villain! Let go of my Lady Paddington!

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Dear dear dear, don't move from where you are, okay? I might accidentally let slip my knife in the wrong place.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: What do you want? There are no toys in this castle that you want.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Yes, there are. It's where you are about to go.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: What do you mean? Are you saying that there are ancient mechanical parts and weapons in this castle that you want?

Name: Canaria
Phrase: I wished there were. Unfortunately, it's not toys I want, but a convenient tool.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: A convenient tool?

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Yes, a tool to make it rain. Someone who failed to be the Guardian of the Giant Tree.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: A tool to make it rain! You're calling the daughter of the lord of this castle a tool!?

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Miss Versailles, stay where you are. She has a hostage.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: ...I'm sorry.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: What are you all doing here in Metro? You didn't come after me, did you?

Name: Yakutsk
Phrase: Of course not. You are talking in your sleep.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: We have come in search of the Guardians of the Giant Trees. The four remaining guardians may be suffering from the same Poison as Ricardo.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: So what? If they are suffering from the Poison?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: We will release them, with the help of Sir Conductor.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Oh I see, you all still have such a strong sense of justice. I'm so dazzled, my eyes are about to melt.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: But be careful, you might just kill the Guardians of the Giant Trees and create big trouble you know? The number of 'failures' with incomplete powers is increasing rapidly thus.
What do you mean by "failures" with incomplete powers? Are you talking about the Divine Children? Or do you mean the Train Knights?

Name: Canaria
Phrase: The losers that are not that big of a deal. Just monsters who think they're human beings. I'm talking about the cute monsters from the otherworlds that don't live here. They are trying to protect the Giant Trees in place of the Guardians.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Trying to protect the Giant Tree instead of the Guardian? The Giant Tree in St. Iris has been purified, right?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: With Ricardo gone, it's no longer immune. Some people might make the mistake of thinking that.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Considered perhaps the Giant Tree is subconsciously inviting them? Maybe that's why there are more and more 'failures' all over the world. You know what they say, 'Put a lid on the trash'.
But that's a contradiction. St. Iris is the only country that doesn't have a Guardian of the Giant Tree. Where are the guardians of the other countries?

Name: Canaria
Phrase: The four Guardians are alive, you know? But they've escaped because of you all.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Wait a minute. So you're saying that the four remaining Giant Trees are defenceless against the Poison?

Name: Canaria
Phrase: That's what it would mean. It means that not all Guardians are as stupid as Ricardo.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Raindrop Princess in this castle here has strong powers. Add a drop of Poison to her imperfect state and she should transform into something interesting.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: So it is Anna's mistress you are after, after all.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Anna? You mean the little rat that the Raindrop Princess loved so much?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: She's not a rat. She is a maid who works in this castle. She served the mistress and was loved by her more than anyone else.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: We know that this castle appeared with the Phantom Mist. We know that Anna is no longer of this world, as well as the poor mistress who makes it rain brings misfortune to this land. We will have to avenge Anna's mistress.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: But she does not deserve to be insulted by evil people like you. Please begone, for you have called Anna a rat.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: The lord of the castle here used to fight against humans. He might be more evil than I am, you know?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I am not asking if the people who lived in the castle here were evil. I am asking you to withdraw your insults against Anna!
Stop it, Victoria. She is not a decent person. It's not a good idea to provoke her any further.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: He's right, you know? If you shout too loudly, my fingers might slip.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: What are your demands? You wouldn't take hostages if you didn't have any.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: You have the key, don't you? Give it to me.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: You can't hide it. You have it around your neck. I can see it.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: ...I have no choice, Lady Paddington's life is more important than these keys.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Why don't you just give me that bunch of keys now?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: You have to let Lady Paddington go first. I promise you that you will get the keys. So put down your weapon first and bring Lady Paddington over here.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Very well, but if you're lying, I'll really kill her, okay?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: Paddy!

Name: Paddington
Phrase: Hawawa! Victoriaaaa~!

Name: Victoria
Phrase: It's all right. I'll never let you go.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Now now, give me the keys quickly.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I know. I'll keep my word.
After confirming that Paddington is safe, Victoria removed the bundle of keys from around her neck and throws it towards Canaria.
But we all must have noticed.
The keys are for opening the dungeon. It is not the keys to the tower that Canaria is trying to open.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: It has numbers on it. Which key will open the small room in the tower?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: It cannot be opened with just one key. Anna told me that the door to the tower has a special mechanism that requires a combination of keys to open it.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Victoria, is that...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: It's all right, Versailles. This is not the place to be reckless.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: (I know what you mean. I'll take care of this.)

Name: Versailles
Phrase: I understand... That's the best way to do it.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I am glad you understand. Canaria is such a strong enemy that we would struggle against her even if we gave it our all. She seems to be more powerful than when you've previously met her, so we don't want to fight her under such adverse conditions.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: So? How do I open the lock?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: The keys are numbered. It is unlocked by passing three odd-numbered keys in quick succession through the keyhole.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Interesting, but not a key one wants to use when they're in a hurry. There are many odd numbers, though.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: The first number is changed depending on the day of the week. I don't even know which number today starts with. I'd have to actually try it out on the keyhole.

Name: Canaria
Phrase: Tsk, what a pain in the ass. Well, whatever. You all can stay here and play in the water.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: She created a Metro Hole by herself!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: That's Gate magic. It's the kind of a teleportation magic Mary uses.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: What horrible magic. It looks like a Metro Hole, but the power I can feel that black door is very different.
Canaria used Gate magic to leave this place. Victoria's tact will probably buy us some time.
But we can't rest easy yet. We... still have to think of a way to get out of here.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: The door won't budge. It's sealed with magic.

Name: Queensway
Phrase: It's Canaria's work. She must have done some sabotage when she left.

Name: Putra
Phrase: By any chance... is the big door back to the Hole also blocked too?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Canaria told us to play in the water together.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Yes, I do like playing in the water? I don't get it, could you make it a bit clearer for me?

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: Then Yoshino will try to explain it better.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: She wants Yoshino and friends to drown.

Name: Putra
Phrase: I see what she meant~

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: You still have time to crack a joooke!? We have to hurry back to check that big door.

Name: Putra
Phrase: Sure, but I'm probably the only one left who can do that now.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Why?

Name: Putra
Phrase: Because the water is just right below our feet.
Putra is right. Most of the stone tower is already submerged. The flooding of the dungeons was not caused by the rain, but by a curse placed on this castle.

Name: Putra
Phrase: I can dive underwater. I can probably go check and come back. Bit difficult to do anything else though. If that big door is closed, I won't be able to open it anyway.

Name: Yoshino
Phrase: It's better not to go. It's not always a case to just go and come back, and even if you can get out into the Hole, if the front door is blocked you're out of luck.

Name: Putra
Phrase: I suppose. I have to consider that the Hole is also flooded...

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: Let's break the wall with magic. Even if we can't open the door, we can break the tower, can't we?
-That's not necessary. We've unlocked the door.

Name: Vivienne
Phrase: What... was that voice?

Name: Victoria
Phrase: That's not Anna's voice.
-We are the ones who have been watching over Anna for many years.\n-Please help those two.\n-Please help them before that monster takes our mistress!

Name: Victoria
Phrase: I don't know who you all are, but thank you.
Victoria put her hand on the door without hesitation. Without using either tools or her feet, she grabbed the door handle and slowly pushed it open.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: It's open!

Name: Queensway
Phrase: Now we have a clear path out.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: No, not yet. We haven't saved Anna and the young lady yet.

Name: Versailles
Phrase: Miss Victoria...

Name: Victoria
Phrase: That's the other tower we can see over there. There is no sign of Canaria. It's now or never if we want to go.

Name: Victoria
Phrase: If we don't save those two, this place will sink to the bottom. Let's go. I am sure we can open the door.
No one objected to Victoria's suggestion.
